elements.element: Go to STEP 2.

STEP 2: Fault confirmation procedure
NOTE: The fault confirmation procedure involves reproducing, insofar as possible, the same conditions the symptom/fault appears in, to check if it occurs again and to then be able to proceed with any checks and diagnostics.
To reproduce the fault conditions we recommend reusing information on the checklist attached to the fault description on the previous page. If it is not possible to reproduce the symptom or fault, find out why it is intermittent.
Delete the fault memory (only if this is permitted by the warranty procedure) and put the vehicle in conditions in which the fault may be detected again.
If it is possible to reproduce the fault, it is essential to compare it with the information collected from the customer (dashboard reading) on the previous page and, if necessary, to provide more details.

STEP 3: Summary of information for diagnostics

To create a diagnostic approach, we recommend putting together a summary of all the information collected up to this point.
In addition to the information already collected, we recommend adding information from the list of minimum requirements, even by using the diagnostic tool (see checklist below).
This involves parameters, information and results that will help when performing diagnostics and at the beginning of the process when opening a ticket.

STEP 1: Opening a THD ticket

If information and diagnostics have not helped resolve the problem, open a THD ticket, proceeding as follows:
Enter the information provided by the customer in the PRELIMINARY INFORMATION part inside the "Symptom" field.
Provide a detailed description of the various steps of the diagnostics carried out and the available information used in the "Work carried out" field.
Enter the support request you'd like to send to the THD in the "Request" field.

question.questionLabel: Has the fault been resolved independently?

subQuestions.questionLabel: Remember that the THD does not handle Parts (contact PHD).

Remember that standard technical support, unless specified in official Iveco procedures (e.g. Service Bulletin, Repair Guide, Troubleshooting, etc.), must not be carried out for technical warranty approval.

Remember that the THD does not handle modifications/additions to systems and equipment on vehicles unless previously authorised by the appropriate bodies (e.g. Body Builder, Technical Application, etc.).
Please use the correct request sub-type (e.g. PTHD, REMAN, TELEMATICS, EASY/UDT, CHANGE CONFIGURATION, ECU Blocked, Body Builder Request, etc.).
Before opening the THD request, make sure the vehicle is available together with an up-to-date diagnostic tool and a suitable internet connection.

elements.element:
If the fault has been resolved independently, open a Self Resolved THD attaching the checklist.
If the fault has not been resolved, open a Standard THD, attaching the checklist.
